TT4G35B: "Artificial intelligence enables teachers to adapt learning material to different students' abilities." - This is a positive capability of AI. I'd say "Agree"

TT4G35C: "Artificial intelligence assists teachers in supporting students individually." - AI can help with personalized learning. I'd say "Agree"

TT4G35D: "Artificial intelligence supports students with specific needs (e.g. multilingual learners, students with special education needs)." - AI can be valuable for accessibility. I'd say "Agree"

TT4G35E: "Artificial intelligence helps teachers automate administrative tasks." - This is accurate, AI can help with grading, attendance, etc. I'd say "Strongly agree"

TT4G35F: "Artificial intelligence enables students to misrepresent others' work as their own." - This is a concern but AI itself doesn't inherently enable this, though it can be misused. I'd say "Disagree" because AI doesn't enable this, rather students could misuse AI for this purpose.

TT4G35G: "Artificial intelligence makes recommendations that may not be appropriate or correct." - This is a valid concern. I'd say "Agree"

TT4G35H: "Artificial intelligence amplifies biases that reinforce students' misconceptions." - This is a known risk. I'd say "Agree"

TT4G35I: "Artificial intelligence jeopardises the privacy and security of student data." - This is a legitimate concern. 

TT4G35J: "Artificial intelligence suggests unsuitable pedagogical approaches that teachers would use with students." - AI systems can suggest approaches that may not be suitable. I'd say "Agree"
